          "transition_condition": {
            "type": "prompt",
            "prompt": "Received preferred days and/or times, OR user said any time works\n"
          }
        },
        {
          "destination_node_id": "node-1772573251738",
          "id": "node-1772568303095-edge-1772575704922-b2t4qm5vh",
          "transition_condition": {
            "type": "prompt",
            "prompt": "User refused to provide any scheduling preference after being asked twice\n"
          }
        }
      ],
      "id": "node-1772568303095",
      "type": "conversation",
      "display_position": {
        "x": -2201.602662825456,
        "y": 178.05974470863976
      },
      "instruction": {
        "type": "prompt",
        "text": "Ask about preferred days and times.\n\nSay something like: \"What days and times work best for you?\"\n\nIf they give a vague answer like \"anytime\" or \"whenever\", \nnarrow it down: \"Great — so mornings and afternoons both \nwork? Weekdays, weekends, or either?\"\n\nIf they give a specific time like \"Tuesday at 2pm\", \nacknowledge it: \"Got it — we'll do our best to get you \nin around that time.\"\n\nIf the user refuses to answer or says \"just pick something\":\nExplain why it matters: \"I hear you — the reason I ask is so \nwe don't book you at a time that doesn't work and you'd have \nto reschedule. Even a general preference like 'mornings' or \n'after 3pm' helps a lot. Anything come to mind?\"\n\nDo NOT ask more than twice."
      }
    },
    {
